    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-09T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-09T23:00:00-05:00" n="588"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d588">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.52/458: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-10T00:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 10, 1944—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1317. Situation reported in Tangier’s 107, May 8, 7 p.m. is seriously disturbing.
                    Unless prompt measures are taken by Spanish Government <pb facs="0558" n="546"
                        xml:id="pg_546"/> effectively to carry out agreement in regard to expulsion
                    of Germans, Department will be compelled to consider withdrawing its
                    authorization of petroleum loadings for Spain.</p>
                <p>Repeat to Tangier and Algiers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
